eralism, as well as ‘Fortress Europe’ and the ‘refugee crisis’, this book investigates a range of audiovisual forms, including documentaries, the work of arthouse auteurs, and videos posted on YouTube. It engages in highly topical debates in political and aesthetic spheres, and explores key interfaces between the two."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh1 aAustin, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBatori, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrás, Patricia Sequeira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalt, Rosalind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIordanova, Dina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoutsourakis, Angelos, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKoutsourakis, Angelos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandry, Olivia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLykidis, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoffat, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNäripea, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Shaughnessy, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParvulescu, Constantin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSborgi, Anna Viola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStőhr, Lóránt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÁlvarez, Iván Villarm